laboratory_examinations.findings: Two hypodense lesions in the liver in segment VIII measuring 1.7 cm and 2.0 cm are unchanged from prior ultrasound and characterized as hemangiomas. A small cyst or hemangioma is seen at the inferior liver. No new liver lesion is identified. Tiny hypodensities in the right kidney measuring up to 8 mm, similar to prior, likely representing cysts. The appendix is filled with stool and air proximate with a normal tip, measuring up to 1.7 cm, with mild adjacent stranding noted.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Two lesions in the liver unchanged from prior ultrasound; tiny hypodensities in the right kidney similar to prior.
